  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "For example, Li et al. [86] present the first extensive evaluation of LLMs for logging statement generation.",
    "Furthermore, Sridhara et al. [131] explore the proficiency of ChatGPT in summarizing logs, achieving promising results surpassing the existing method.",
    "Li et al. [87] propose to incorporate static context into code prompt and employ a self-refinement manner to further rectify previous errors.",
    "Another important field in logging activities is log parsing, which aims at extracting structured templates and parameters from raw log messages to provide insights for developers [56,61,172].",
    "To facilitate the effectiveness of LLM for log parsing, [160] leverages LLM and in-context learning (ICL) for log template extraction and another work [70] improves log parsing by ICL and parsing cache.LLMs are also beneficial in generating test cases from natural language descriptions, which enhances cooperation between software developers and testers."
